The paper deals with Distributed Constraint Optimization Problems (DCOPs), which are a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) that deals with multi-agent coordination and resource allocation problems. The paper also mentions the use of logic programming technologies, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a general constraint solver, which is related to Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA).
